  "text": "The datasource plugin query path in grafana/grafana comprises three main components:\n\n## Query Request Handler\n\nThe request path starts at two entry points:\n1. **Plugin Aggregator Path** (`pkg/aggregator/apiserver/plugin/query.go:QueryDataHandler`) - Handles HTTP requests for plugin data plane services, decodes the QueryDataRequest, validates the datasource reference, and retrieves the plugin context.\n2. **Datasource Registry Path** (`pkg/registry/apis/datasource/sub_query.go:subQueryREST.Connect`) - Implements the `/datasources/{uid}/query` REST endpoint, binds the query request, and dispatches to the plugin client.\n3. **Query API Path** (`pkg/registry/apis/query/query.go:queryREST.Connect`) - Main query API handler that orchestrates the full query pipeline including expression service and multi-plugin queries.\n\n## Plugin Backend Query Dispatch\n\nThe query is dispatched through a multi-layer architecture:\n1. **Query Client Handler** (`pkg/registry/apis/query/client/plugin.go:pluginClient.QueryData`) - Validates permissions and datasource existence, creates QueryDataRequest with plugin context.\n2. **Manager Client** (`pkg/plugins/manager/client/client.go:Service.QueryData`) - Routes queries to the registered plugin instance, handles frame RefID assignment.\n3. **Plugin Registry** (`pkg/plugins/manager/registry/in_memory.go:InMemory.Plugin`) - Looks up the plugin by ID from the registry.\n4. **GRPC Plugin** (`pkg/plugins/backendplugin/grpcplugin/grpc_plugin.go:grpcPlugin.QueryData`) - Manages the GRPC connection lifecycle and delegates to the GRPC client.\n5. **GRPC Client V2** (`pkg/plugins/backendplugin/grpcplugin/client_v2.go:ClientV2.QueryData`) - Converts backend QueryDataRequest to protobuf, sends to the plugin, and converts the response back with error handling.\n6. **Core Plugin** (`pkg/plugins/backendplugin/coreplugin/core_plugin.go:corePlugin.QueryData`) - Handles built-in plugins by delegating to the QueryDataHandler in the core plugin implementation.\n\n## Query Response Transformation\n\nResponses are transformed through:\n1. **Response Type Wrapping** - The backend.QueryDataResponse is wrapped in `pkg/apis/query/v0alpha1/query.go:QueryDataResponse` with TypeMeta and ObjectMeta for Kubernetes API compatibility.\n2. **Response Code Calculation** (`pkg/apis/query/v0alpha1/query.go:GetResponseCode`) - Determines appropriate HTTP status code (200/400/500) based on error presence and error source.\n3. **Error Handling** (`pkg/registry/apis/datasource/queryconvert.go`) - Query conversion handler for transforming queries between formats.\n4. **Middleware Processing** (`pkg/registry/apis/datasource/middleware.go:contextualMiddlewares`) - Applies response limit middleware and AWS SigV4 authentication if needed.\n\n## Supporting Infrastructure\n\n**Plugin Context Provider** (`pkg/registry/apis/datasource/plugincontext.go:PluginContextWrapper`) - Creates PluginContext with datasource settings and Grafana configuration.\n\n**DataSourceAPIBuilder** (`pkg/registry/apis/datasource/register.go`) - Registers the datasource API endpoints including the /query, /health, /resource, and /queryconvert subresources.\n\n**Querier Interface** (`pkg/registry/apis/datasource/querier.go`) - Abstracts the query execution with DefaultQuerier delegating to the plugin client.\n\nThe complete flow routes a query request from HTTP handler → datasource query endpoint → plugin client → plugin registry → GRPC plugin/core plugin → backend plugin handler → response transformation → HTTP response with appropriate status code."
