in implementation.\n\n## Query Response Transformation\n\nResponses are transformed through:\n1. **Response Type Wrapping** - The backend.QueryDataResponse is wrapped in `pkg/apis/query/v0alpha1/query.go:QueryDataResponse` with TypeMeta and ObjectMeta for Kubernetes API compatibility.\n2. **Response Code Calculation** (`pkg/apis/query/v0alpha1/query.go:GetResponseCode`) - Determines appropriate HTTP status code (200/400/500) based on error presence and error source.\n3. **Error Handling** (`pkg/registry/apis/datasource/queryconvert.go`) - Query conversion handler for transforming queries between formats.\n4. **Middleware Processing** (`pkg/registry/apis/datasource/middleware.go:contextualMiddlewares`) - Applies response limit middleware and AWS SigV4 authentication if needed.\n\n## Supporting Infrastructure\n\n**Plugin Context Provider** (`pkg/registry/apis/datasource/plugincontext.go:PluginContextWrapper`) - Creates PluginContext with datasource settings and Grafana configuration.\n\n**DataSourceAPIBuilder** (`pkg/registry/apis/datasource/register.go`) - Registers the datasource API endpoints including the /query, /health, /resource, and /queryconvert subresources.\n\n**Querier Interface** (`pkg/registry/apis/datasource/querier.go`) - Abstracts the query execution with DefaultQuerier delegating to the plugin client.\n\nThe complete flow routes a query request from HTTP handler → datasource query endpoint → plugin client → plugin registry → GRPC plugin/core plugin → backend plugin handler → response transformation → HTTP response with appropriate status code."
